## ðŸ–¥ï¸ Option 3: Native Systemd Service (Linux)

### Make CHIMERA a System Service

```bash
# 1. Create service file
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/chimera.service
```

```ini
[Unit]
Description=CHIMERA AUTARCH - Self-Evolving AI Orchestrator
After=network.target

[Service]
Type=simple
User=YOUR_USERNAME
WorkingDirectory=/home/YOUR_USERNAME/Drox_AI
Environment="PATH=/home/YOUR_USERNAME/Drox_AI/venv/bin"
ExecStart=/home/YOUR_USERNAME/Drox_AI/venv/bin/python chimera_autarch.py
Restart=always
RestartSec=10

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

```bash
# 2. Enable and start
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable chimera
sudo systemctl start chimera

# 3. Check status
sudo systemctl status chimera

# 4. View logs
sudo journalctl -u chimera -f

# Now CHIMERA runs independently on boot!
```

